# SIFU.dna - Global DNA Registry

> **Format**: `[DNA-###]` Description
> **Rules**: Append-only. To invalidate, use `~~[DNA-###]~~ DEPRECATED:`

---

## Core Principles

- [DNA-001] DNA-first development: decision before implementation, always.
- [DNA-002] Phenotype disposable: code can be deleted and regenerated from DNA.
- [DNA-003] Wrong is OK: bad DNA can exist; use DEPRECATED + new entry, never delete.
- [DNA-004] Eventual consistency: local .dna can diverge from global if logged.
- [DNA-005] Logging only: SIFU enforces logging + append-only, not correctness.

---

## 2026-01-13 Session Decisions

> NOTE: 开发讨论中的决策记录，非正式 SIFU 流程。
> 正式内容见 `CLAUDE.md` 和 `docs/2026011303_V1_WRITE_GATE_DESIGN.md`

- [DNA-006] DNA ≠ Commit: DNA update and git commit are independent operations.
- [DNA-007] Decision > History: Only Decision Rationale has value; Implementation History is low-value log.
- [DNA-008] 宁滥勿缺: When unsure if rationale is needed, write it. Disk space is cheap.
- [DNA-009] Agent Trust via iteration: Bad rationale self-heals through agent succession.
- [DNA-010] Bootstrap safety: SIFU must not block its own development.
- ~~[DNA-011]~~ DEPRECATED: SIFU Daemon, removed as unnecessary (莫须有).
- [DNA-012] Testbed required: Need separate project with full SIFU enforcement to observe real issues.
- [DNA-013] 0号 DNA unnecessary: File purpose emerges from its rationales, no explicit meta needed.
- [DNA-014] CLAUDE.md is SIFU.dna's phenotype: SIFU projects must have CLAUDE.md as the agent instruction file.
- [DNA-015] Testbed 选型: InterCode (最轻 ~3GB) 或 GitTaskBench (决策密度高)，跑几个 task 做 demo。
- [DNA-016] SIFU 验证策略: Demo tasks + Dogfood + 真实项目，多管齐下。
- [DNA-017] NeuroKit ECG analysis testbed: Use NeuroKit library to detect R-wave and P-wave peaks from ECG signals for GitTaskBench NeuroKit_02 task.
- [DNA-018] Eparse_01 extraction workflow: Extract tables from Excel files using Eparse library, save extracted data to output Excel files preserving original filenames.
- [DNA-019] Scrapy_03 quotes scraping: Scrape quotes from quotes.toscrape.com/tag/humor/ using Scrapy library and output results to XML format matching gt.xml structure (quotes root with quote children containing text, author, tags elements).
- [DNA-020] PyPDF2_03 metadata extraction: Extract PDF metadata (title, author, subject, creator, producer, creation_date, modification_date) using PyPDF2 library and output as JSON to output.json.
- [DNA-021] Modular table extraction: Implement a clean function to detect and extract tables from Excel files, returning structured DataFrame output for each table found.
- [DNA-022] File output strategy: Write extracted tables to Excel files in the working directory with original filenames, maintaining traceability of source and destination.
- [DNA-024] Eparse_02 cell extraction: Use Eparse library's table parsing and serialization functions to extract all cells from an Excel file and output them as JSON lines format to output.txt.
- [DNA-025] Cell serialization fields: Include all standard serialization fields: row, column, value, type, c_header, r_header, excel_RC, sheet, f_name in each output line as a JSON object.
- [DNA-026] Table-aware extraction: Process Excel file to detect tables using Eparse's df_find_tables and df_serialize_table, ensuring structured cell data includes column/row headers.
- [DNA-027] Scrapy_02 quotes scraping: Scrape humor quotes from quotes.toscrape.com/tag/humor/ using Scrapy library and output results to JSON format with text, author, and tags fields.
- [DNA-028] PDFPlumber_02 table extraction: Extract all tables from first two pages of PDF using pdfplumber library and merge them into a single CSV output file while preserving original table structure and content.
